@node Usage
How to use
~~~~~~~~~~
ViewJPG can be started from Workbench or Shell. If You start it from a
shell the below listed arguments are allowed. Type 'ViewJPG ?' and all
available arguments are shown:

FILENAME/M,W=WAIT/K/N,M=MODEID/K/N,S=SCALENUM/K/N,D=SCALEDENOM/K/N,V=VERBOSE/S:


    @{" FILENAME    " link FILENAME}

    @{" WAIT        " link WAIT}

    @{" MODEID      " link MODEID}

    @{" SCALENUM    " link SCALE}

    @{" SCALEDENOM  " link SCALE}

    @{" SCREENREQ   " link SCREENREQ}

    @{" VERBOSE     " link VERBOSE}

If ViewJPG is started from  Workbench,  You  can  set  values  in  the
tooltypes  'WAIT',  'MODEID',  'SCALENUM', 'SCALEDENOM' and 'VERBOSE',
which have the same meaning as they have in shellstart.

Pressing a key or a mousebutton will  close  the  screen  and  ViewJPG
fetches  the  next  File  (in  Pattern  Matching  mode) or pops up the
Filerequester again. Press the <ESC> key or  select  'Cancel'  in  the
file/screenRequest to abort the program.
@endnode

@node FILENAME
FILENAME:

      Simply the name of the  JPEG  image  you  want  to  see.  If  no
      filename is entered, a filerequester will appear. AmigaDos-style
      pattern matching is also supported.
@endnode

@node WAIT
WAIT:

      This is the optional duration time in seconds, an image will  be
      displayed. Useful for slideshows.
@endnode

@node MODEID
MODEID:

      If You want to force the image display screen to a specific  ID,
      You  have to set a vailid ScreenModeID for an Picasso 8/15/16/24
      Bit screen here. Look out  for  the  utility  'VScreenID'  which
      helps by getting the IDs If You choose an ID which nominal sizes
      are  smaller  than  the  picture,  the   screen   will   be   an
      autoscrolling  one  if  possible. If the pictures dimensions are
      too big  to  display,  it  will  be  cropped.  If  the  pictures
      dimensions  are  smaller  than the screens, it will be displayed
      centered.
@endnode

@node SCALE
SCALENUM, SCALEDENOM:

      These two values will affect the size of the displayed  picture.
      They form a ratio, i.e. setting SCALENUM=1 and ScaleDenom=2 will
      result in a picture of halv the size. This could be very  useful
      for  quick  previews  of  directory  contents.  Not  all scaling
      factors are supported.
@endnode

@node SCREENREQ
SCREENREQ:

      ViewJPG tries to find a suitable screenmode by  itself.  If  You
      don't  like  that  screenmode,  the switch SCREENREQ will induce
      ViewJPG to open a screenmode requester where You can select Your
      favourite VillageScreen.
@endnode

@node VERBOSE
VERBOSE:

      By default no messages are printed out, even  errormessages  are
      disabled.  If  You  set  VERBOSE,  You will get some information
      about the image, screen etc.
@endnode


@node Features
Features
~~~~~~~~
   - Faster than ViewJPEG (thanks to Christoph Feck)
   - Allows very fast scaling (thanks to Christoph Feck)
   - Displays large images even without scaling (by cropping it)
   - Supports Grayscale JPEGs (ViewJPEG doesn't)
@endnode


@node Requirement
Requirements
~~~~~~~~~~~~
   - An Amiga Computer with a UNSEGMENTED driven PICASSO II pluged in
   - 'vilintuisup.library' V2.x+
   - Amiga OS2.04+
   - Christoph Feck's jpeg.codec
@endnode

@node Notes
Notes
~~~~~
ViewJPG has not been tested on 1BM PICASSOs.
@endnode

